{{Quote|You ever run a job out to Zekulae, at the heart of the Zeemacht Cluster, lift your eyes from the comm for a minute. You'll be staring up at a matrix of bright orange and red giants, neutron stars, pulsars, and blue stragglers the Zeku call the Cosm's Well. It's about the most beautiful thing I've ever seen that I couldn't buy or sell, and that's saying something.|[[Crix Q5 Baobab]]|<ref name="TEA">''[[The Essential Atlas]]''</ref>}}
The '''Zeku''' were the inhabitants of the [[Planet/Legends|planet]] [[Zekulae]],<ref name="DOH">''[[Jedi Apprentice: The Death of Hope]]''</ref> located in the [[Zeemacht Cluster/Legends|Zeemacht Cluster]] of the [[Inner Rim/Legends|Inner Rim]].<ref name="EAOC">{{SW|url=news/star-wars-the-essential-atlas-online-companion|text=''Star Wars: The Essential Atlas'' Online Companion|int=Star Wars: The Essential Atlas Online Companion}}</ref> Their planet was a barren world, noted for its dark, rich mineral soil, studded with [[Color/Legends|blue]] [[Crystal/Legends|crystals]]. Its soil was so fine, that it was everpresent on the planet. The Zeku government took a relaxed approach to laws, and as such, it was not uncommon for disputes to be resolved through physical force or [[Blaster/Legends|blasters]].<ref name="DOH" />

Visible from Zekulae was a [[Star cluster/Legends|globular cluster]] of [[Orange giant|orange]] and [[Red giant/Legends|red]] [[Giant star|giants]], [[Neutron star/Legends|neutron stars]], [[Pulsar/Legends|pulsars]], and [[blue straggler]]s which the Zeku called [[Cosm's Well/Legends|Cosm's Well]].<ref name="TEA" />

==Behind the scenes==
The Zeku were created by [[Jude Watson]] for her young adults novel, ''[[Jedi Apprentice: The Death of Hope]]'', published in [[2001]]. The novel leaves it unclear whether the term Zeku is a [[Species/Legends|species]] or a demonym.

